  date          = {2002},
  title         = {L'anthropomorphisme, voie d'acces privilegiee au vivant. L'apport de Hans Jonas},
  number        = {3},
  pages         = {437-465},
  volume        = {100},
  abstract      = {To what extent is it legitimate and necessary, in
knowledge of extrahuman life, to appeal to what one knows
as a human being, by one's own belonging to life, and to
what extent should one beware of analogies with human
experience? Contrary to the pure and simple exclusion of
all anthropomorphism decreed by modern science, we plead
here, on the basis of a commentary on the passages devoted
to this topic by Jonas in his writings on "philosophical
biology", for its partial rehabilitation and for a
