  publisher     = {Rowman and Littlefield},
  abstract      = {This article considers John Rist's dating of the Poetics
after the Eudemian and before the Nicomachean Ethics. I
explore the intuitive reasons for thinking that the Poetics
may have led to changes we can identify in Aristotle's
ethical views on the topics of I) voluntariness and II) the
role of contingency or {\tt{}"{}}moral luck{\tt{}"{}} in a
good life. However, on each issue I argue that the correct
account is more complex and doubtful than the intuitively
plausible picture of a neat development suggests. I also
