  issn            = {0002-953X},
  issue           = {4},
  pages           = {505--524},
  pubstate        = {ppublish},
  volume          = {156},
  abstract        = {The American Journal of Psychiatry has received a number
of letters in response to my earlier "Framework" article
(1). Some of these are reprinted elsewhere in this issue,
and I have answered them briefly there. However, one issue
raised by some letters deserves a more detailed answer, and
that relates to whether biology is at all relevant to
psychoanalysis. To my mind, this issue is so central to the
future of psychoanalysis that it cannot be addressed with a
brief comment. I therefore have written this article in an
attempt to outline the importance of biology for the future
of psychoanalysis.},
