  date      = {1933},
  title     = {Beitrage zur Konstitution und Anthropologie der Mongolen},
  number    = {(1)},
  pages     = {52--76},
  volume    = {18},
  abstract  = {The studies, carried on in Moscow in 1930-1931, are
representatives of the principal types of Mongol (Kalka,
Buriat and Kalmuck), comprising 156 [male][male] (17-34
yrs.) and 65 [female][female] (16-31 yrs.). The principal
subjects of investigation are listed under: (1) Dynamics of
physical development (puberty, growth, weight and chest
girth, leg-stem, head) ; (2) observations in relation to
sexual maturity (genitals, hairiness, type of body-build
Stefko) ; (3) physical type of Mongolian adult
("dysgenital" type, normal types) ; (4) stature, body
proportions, dimensions of head (head, face, ear form,
pigmentation). It is pointed out that, with some
reservation, there occurs a certain community of somatic
and morphologic distinctions in the various Mongolian
groups, and that conditions of "fetalization" (Bolk) are
countered by such as "maturisation" (prevailingly in the
Turk varieties). || ABSTRACT AUTHORS: B. Oetteking},
