  producer        = {Casati, Francesco},
  abstract        = {Andrei Gorchakov is a misanthropic Russian scholar
studying the life of an exiled Russian composer who
committed suicide. With the help of his beautiful guide,
Eugenia, Andrei visits spiritual and religious sites on the
track of the late composer's legacy. Haunted by the ghost
of the composer's remembrance, Andrei soon finds himself
the prey of a gloomy nostalgia for his Russian mother
country, only to find rescue in the figure of a madman,
Domenico, whom he meets at St. Catherine's pool, a sacred
site in Siena. Domenico, an ex-professor who once locked
his family away for seven years in the expectation of
Armageddon, now conducts a apparently insane existence,
believing that if he can go across the pool with a burning
candle, he can rescue all of humanity.},
  date            = {1983},
  langid          = {russian},
